├── src/
│   ├── app/
│   │   ├── page.js                    # Home/Landing page
│   │   ├── create/                    # AR creation interface
│   │   ├── ar/[shortCode]/            # AR viewer (image-based)
│   │   ├── sticker/[code]/            # Sticker AR viewer
│   │   ├── admin/                     # Admin dashboard
│   │   ├── api/                       # API routes
│   │   │   ├── experience/            # Create AR keychain
│   │   │   ├── sticker-experience/    # Create sticker AR
│   │   │   ├── admin-auth/            # Login endpoint
│   │   │   └── track/                 # Analytics tracking
│   │   └── layout.js                  # Root layout
│   ├── components/                    # React components
│   │   ├── StickerARScene.jsx         # MindAR sticker viewer
│   │   ├── WebXRScene.jsx             # WebXR viewer
│   │   ├── ImageUpload.jsx            # Cloudinary upload
│   │   └── CameraPermissionScreen.jsx # Permission UI
│   ├── lib/
│   │   ├── prisma.js                  # Prisma client
│   │   └── utils.js                   # Utility functions
│   └── middleware.js                  # Auth middleware
├── prisma/
│   ├── schema.prisma                  # Database schema
│   └── migrations/                    # Database migrations
├── public/                            # Static assets
├── next.config.mjs                    # Next.js configuration
├── package.json                       # Dependencies
└── .env.example                       # Environment template
```

## 🎨 Technology Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16+ (React 19)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL with Prisma ORM
- **AR Libraries**:
  - Three.js (3D rendering)
  - MindAR (Image recognition)
  - WebXR API (Spatial AR)
- **Uploads**: Cloudinary
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4
- **Authentication**: Session cookies (admin)

## 📡 API Routes

### `/api/experience` (POST)
Create a new AR keychain experience.

**Headers**: `Content-Type: application/json`

**Body**:
```json
{
  "message": "Your custom message",
  "imageUrl": "https://cloudinary-url.com/image.jpg"
}
```

**Response** (201):
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "shortCode": "a1b2c3",
  "message": "AR experience created successfully!"
}
```

### `/api/sticker-experience` (POST)
Create a sticker AR experience (admin only).

**Headers**:
```
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: YOUR_ADMIN_API_KEY
```

**Body**:
```json
{
  "targetImage": "https://cloudinary-url.com/sticker.jpg",
  "assetUrl": "https://cdn.example.com/model.glb",
  "message": "Optional message"
}
```

### `/api/track` (POST)
Track AR experience scans (non-critical).

**Body**:
```json
{
  "shortCode": "a1b2c3",
  "type": "keychain"
}
```

### `/api/admin-auth` (POST)
Admin login endpoint.

**Body**:
```json
{
  "password": "ADMIN_PASSWORD"
}
```

## 🚢 Deployment

### Vercel (Recommended)

1. Push code to GitHub
2. Import to Vercel
3. Set environment variables in Vercel dashboard
4. Deploy

```bash
# or use Vercel CLI
vercel
```

### Self-Hosted

```bash
# Build for production
npm run build

# Start production server
npm start
```

## 🔒 Security Checklist

- [ ] Change `ADMIN_PASSWORD` from default
- [ ] Generate new `ADMIN_SESSION_TOKEN` and `ADMIN_API_KEY`
- [ ] Set `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` to your production domain
- [ ] Use HTTPS in production
- [ ] Validate all user inputs (implemented)
- [ ] Use secure database credentials
- [ ] Configure CORS properly

## 📊 Database

### Models

**ARExperience** (Keychains)
- `id`: Unique identifier
- `shortCode`: Human-readable code
- `message`: Custom message
- `imageUrl`: Image URL
- `isActive`: Active flag
- `scanCount`: Analytics
- `createdAt`, `updatedAt`: Timestamps

**StickerExperience** (Stickers)
- `id`: Unique identifier
- `code`: Human-readable code (prefixed with "s-")
- `targetImage`: Sticker image URL
- `assetUrl`: 3D model URL (optional)
- `message`: Custom message
- `isActive`: Active flag
- `scanCount`: Analytics
- `createdAt`, `updatedAt`: Timestamps

## 🧪 Testing

```bash
# Run linter
